<!-- ABOUT THE PACK -->
<section class="about-pack">
  <div class="ap-inner">
    <div class="ap-img">
      <img class="ap-img-main" src="{{ 'lb-blueprint-shop-blueprint-028.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Lacquer Bru artist at work" width="1200" height="800">
      <div class="ap-img-tag"><span>16+ Years of Aerosol Culture</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="ap-txt">
      <span class="section-label">Why These Brushes Are Different</span>
      <h2 class="section-h2">Built From the Inside Out</h2>
      <p>Most brush packs are built by designers. The Flare Pack was built by a <strong>graffiti artist</strong> &mdash; someone who has been pushing letters, portraits, and large scale work across walls, canvases, and tablets for over 16 years.</p>
      <p>Every brush in this pack started as a problem. A stroke that didn't feel right. A texture that was missing. A tool that didn't exist yet. The Flare Pack is the direct result of building the tools needed for real artistic work &mdash; and making them available to every creative who needs the same.</p>
      <p>These are not demo brushes. They are <strong>working tools</strong> from an active studio &mdash; tested under real deadlines, across real projects, and refined until they felt exactly right.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

